name Spicy Asparagus Curry with Veal Meatballs
serves 4
tags main, soup, meat, asian, spring
related Thailändischer Spargeleintopf mit Ananas und Chiliöl

# Mise en place

- 2 bunches spring onions
Cut 50g of the light green parts into fine rings, cut the rest into larger pieces.
Keep separate.
-> spring onion rings
-> spring onion pieces

- 500 g green asparagus
@nodep
Peel the lower third, cut off the woody ends and cut diagonally into 6 cm pieces.
-> green asparagus

- 500 g white asparagus
@nodep
Peel all around, cut off the woody ends, halve lengthways and cut diagonally into 6 cm
pieces.
-> white asparagus

- 1 "unwaxed lemon"
@nodep
Finely zest the lemon and squeeze out {2} tbsp of juice.
-> lemon zest and juice

- 50 g peanuts
@nodep
Roughly chop.
-> peanuts

# Meatballs

- 200 g minced veal
- 1 tbsp dark sesame oil
- 40 g desiccated coconut
- 1 egg
- 10 g sesame seeds
- "ground cumin"
- salt
- "cayenne pepper"
= spring onion rings
Knead the mince with the spring onion rings, sesame oil, 30g of the coconut, egg, cumin,
salt and cayenne. Shape into {16} small balls. Mix the remaining coconut with the sesame
seeds and roll the balls in the mixture.

Fry the meatballs in oil on each side over medium heat for 5 minutes until golden brown.
-> meatballs

# Curry

- 2 cloves garlic
- 50 g butter
- 2 tbsp curry powder
- 200 ml plum wine
- 400 ml chicken stock
- 3 tbsp oil
= spring onion pieces
= white asparagus
= green asparagus
Peel and crush the garlic. Gently sauté the spring onion pieces in the butter over low
heat. Quickly stir in the garlic and curry powder, then pour in the plum wine and stock.
Add the white asparagus and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, adding the green asparagus
after 5 minutes. Season with salt.
-> curry

= lemon zest and juice
= peanuts
= meatballs
@ curry
Stir the lemon juice and zest into the curry and ladle into bowls. Top with the meatballs
and scatter over the peanuts.
